  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div class=\"qti-layout-row\"> <div class=\"qti-layout-col12\"> <div class=\"prompt\"> <p class=\"dap_body\">The function&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"L\"><math alttext=\"L\"><mi>L</mi></math></span>&nbsp;is a linear transformation of vectors defined by&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"L open parentheses vector v close parentheses equals A vector v\"><math alttext=\"L open parentheses vector v close parentheses equals A vector v\"><mi>L</mi><mfenced><mover><mi>v</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mover><mi>v</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math></span>,&nbsp;where&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\"><mi>A</mi></math></span>&nbsp;is a transformation matrix.&nbsp;If matrix&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\"><mi>A</mi></math></span>&nbsp;is defined as&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"A 2 by 2 matrix. Row 1 column 1 is negative one half. Row 1 column 2 is negative fraction numerator square root of 3 and denominator 2 end fraction. Row 2 column 1 is fraction numerator square root of 3 and denominator 2 end fraction. Row 2 column 2 is negative one half.\"><math alttext=\"A 2 by 2 matrix. Row 1 column 1 is negative one half. Row 1 column 2 is negative fraction numerator square root of 3 and denominator 2 end fraction. Row 2 column 1 is fraction numerator square root of 3 and denominator 2 end fraction. Row 2 column 2 is negative one half.\"><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math></span>, which of the following describes the linear transformation?</p> </div> </div> </div>\n",
    "answer": "C-12840",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"dap_body\">The linear transformation is a rotation by&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"pi over 6\"><math alttext=\"pi over 6\"><mfrac><mi>π</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math></span>&nbsp;radians counterclockwise about the origin.</p>",
        "value": "A-12838"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"dap_body\">The linear transformation is a rotation by&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"pi over 3\"><math alttext=\"pi over 3\"><mfrac><mi>π</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></span>&nbsp;radians counterclockwise about the origin.</p>",
        "value": "B-12839"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"dap_body\">The linear transformation is a rotation by&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"fraction numerator 2 pi over denominator 3 end fraction\"><math alttext=\"fraction numerator 2 pi over denominator 3 end fraction\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></span>&nbsp;radians counterclockwise about the origin.</p>",
        "value": "C-12840"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"dap_body\">The linear transformation is a rotation by&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"fraction numerator 5 pi over denominator 6 end fraction\"><math alttext=\"fraction numerator 5 pi over denominator 6 end fraction\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math></span>&nbsp;radians counterclockwise about the origin.</p>",
        "value": "D-12841"
      }
    ]
